  canonicalUrl="/landscapers/missed-call-text-back/"
  channelName="Missed Call Text Back"
  tradeName="Landscaper"
  tradeNamePlural="Landscapers"
  tradeSlug="landscapers"
  headline="Missed Call Text Back for Landscaping Businesses"
  accentWord="Landscaping Businesses"
  subhead="A homeowner calls about a complete rear garden build — natural stone patio, retaining walls, planting, and garden lighting. You are operating a mini digger levelling a plot on the other side of town, engine roaring, cab vibrating. The call goes to voicemail. Without Missed Call Text Back, she hangs up and calls the next landscaper in her search results. With it, she receives a text within six seconds: 'Thank you for calling. We are on site and will call you back shortly.' She replies with 'it is about a garden makeover in Witney — roughly 20m x 8m.' You call her at lunch with the complete picture."
  scenario="It is 9:20am on a Saturday in May — your busiest month. You are compacting a freshly laid sub-base for a large porcelain paved terrace in a garden in Henley, dust billowing, ear defenders on, the sun already warm. Your phone is on the dashboard of the pickup. A couple in Marlow calls. They have been planning a garden transformation for months — they want a limestone patio with a built-in barbecue area, raised Corten steel planters, ornamental grasses, a new lawn, and festoon lighting. Their budget is around £25,000 and they want to start in June. Without Missed Call Text Back, they leave a voicemail. At 5pm you are exhausted, covered in dust, and have four voicemails from the day. You call the Marlow couple back at 6pm but they have already booked a site visit with another landscaper who answered at 10am. With Missed Call Text Back, the couple receives a text six seconds after hanging up: 'Thank you for calling [your company]. We are on site today and will call you back as soon as possible. If your garden project is urgent, please reply with the details.' The wife replies: 'No rush — we want a full garden makeover at our house in Marlow. Around £25k budget, hoping to start June. Can you do a site visit?' At 12:30pm you check your phone, see the lead summary with the budget, the scope, the address, and the start date — and call them before you eat your sandwich. You book a Sunday morning site visit and the £25,000 project is yours."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/missed-call-text-back/"
  tradePageUrl="/landscapers/ai-receptionist/"
